The Agbado-Ijaiye Police Station opposite Ebenezer Comprehensive College along Agbado road in Ojokoro Local Council De­velopment Area (LCDA) of Lagos State has built an administrative office that would accommodate all of­ficers at the station. Also a building for (PCRC) has been given a face lift. A source said the building construction which began in March last year had pro­vided a befitting face lift and improved the station tremen­dously under the watchful eyes of Divisional Police Of­ficer DPO, Chief Superinten­dent of Police Gbenga Ogun­shakin. NiMET Warns Of Extreme Heats As Temperature Rises Across States Yobe Commends AFRYDEV For Training GBV Survivors According to a reliable source, when the building is put in use it would provide enough offices for the police officers to perform their daily duties. Some of the police officers who spoke to Daily Indepen­dent said the new building and renovation was initiat­ed by the Divisional Police Officer Gbenga Ogunshakin when he resumed office last year. They said the proactive measure taken by the DPO was a welcome development for the station and community in the area. When completed the building will accommo­date more officers CSP Ogunshakin has promised that the building would be completed with nec­essary furniture in place.